[medium] src/views/system-security-plans/partials/StatementByComponent.vue:187 (correctness vs. the actual SDK/library)
The inline by-component editor exits edit mode immediately after emitting save, before the parent PUT has succeeded. If handleSaveStatementByComponent catches a failed request, the parent data and server remain unchanged, but this component still renders localComponent.description/status in read mode, so the row shows unsaved data after an error toast and can mislead the user into thinking the update persisted.
Suggested fix: Only leave edit mode and display the draft after a successful persistence path. For example, have the parent own the async save state/result and pass a success callback/promise-equivalent prop, or keep the editor open on save until the parent updates the byComponent prop; on failure, reset localComponent from props or remain in edit mode with the draft clearly unsaved.
Guidance: In src/views/system-security-plans/partials/StatementByComponent.vue, save() emits the draft and immediately calls setEditing(false). Because emits are not awaitable here, handleSaveStatementByComponent in src/views/system-security-plans/SystemSecurityPlanControlImplementationView.vue can fail and leave props.byComponent unchanged while this child still renders localComponent in read mode. Fix the child so read mode always displays the persisted prop, not the unsaved draft. Specifically: keep localComponent only as the edit draft; in the non-editing template, render props.byComponent.description and props.byComponent.implementationStatus instead of localComponent.description/localComponent.implementationStatus. Add separate read-only computed values such as persistedImplementationStatusDisplayLabel based on props.byComponent.implementationStatus?.state; do not reuse implementationStatusDisplayLabel if it reads localComponent. Keep the edit form bound to localComponent. In save(), after emit('save', normalizeByComponentImplementationStatus(cloneByComponent(localComponent.value))), either reset localComponent.value = cloneByComponent(props.byComponent) before setEditing(false), or rely on the existing prop watcher, but make sure the read-mode DOM cannot show localComponent after Save. Do not change the @save event name, the parent handler route/API URL, or the JSON payload shape. Add a test in src/views/system-security-plans/partials/__tests__/StatementByComponent.spec.ts that edits the description, triggers Save without changing the byComponent prop, and asserts the component read mode still shows the original props.byComponent.description rather than the draft. Also keep/adjust the Cancel test so both Cancel and failed-save/no-parent-update paths prove drafts do not leak into read mode.
